## Description
Adding controller APIs to fetch brokers information
Per issue: https://github.com/apache/incubator-pinot/issues/5682

Sample output:
```
➜ curl localhost:9000/brokers | jq .
{
  "tenants": {
    "DefaultTenant": [
      "Broker_127.0.0.1_8000"
    ]
  },
  "tables": {
    "airlineStats": [
      "Broker_127.0.0.1_8000"
    ]
  }
}

```
```
➜ curl localhost:9000/brokers/tenants | jq .
{
  "DefaultTenant": [
    "Broker_127.0.0.1_8000"
  ]
}
```
```
➜ curl localhost:9000/brokers/tenants/DefaultTenant | jq .
[
  "Broker_127.0.0.1_8000"
]
```
```
➜ curl localhost:9000/brokers/tables | jq .
{
  "airlineStats": [
    "Broker_127.0.0.1_8000"
  ]
}
```
```
➜ curl "localhost:9000/brokers/tables/airlineStats?type=OFFLINE" | jq .
[
  "Broker_127.0.0.1_8000"
]
```
```
➜ curl "localhost:9000/brokers/tables/airlineStats?type=REALTIME" | jq .
[
  "Broker_127.0.0.1_8000"
]
```
```
➜ curl localhost:9000/brokers/tables/airlineStats | jq .
[
  "Broker_127.0.0.1_8000"
]
```
```
➜ curl localhost:9000/brokers/tables/airlineStats1 | jq .
{
  "code": 404,
  "error": "Table 'airlineStats1' not found."
}

```
## Release Notes
Adding Controller APIs to fetch brokers information:
```
// Return all the {state} brokers mapping of tenants/tables
GET /brokers?state={online|offline}

// Return all the {state} brokers mapping per tenants
GET /brokers/tenants?state={online|offline}

// Return {state} brokers for a given {tenant}, returns all brokers if state is not specified.
GET /brokers/tenants/{tenant}?state={online|offline}

// Return all the {state} brokers mapping per table
GET /brokers/tables?state={online|offline}

// Return {state} brokers for a given {table}_{type}, returns all brokers if state is not specified.
GET /brokers/tables/{table}?type={REALTIME|OFFLINE}&?state={online|offline}
```

## Description
Add TransformConfigs list to IngestionConfig. This is based on discussion in Extensions in the Filtering design doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Cahnas3nh0XErETH0KHLaecN6xCnRVYWNKO3rDn7qcI/edit#heading=h.gr3yby6x7mlv

## Release Notes
Transform functions can be set in the table config instead of schema. In a future release, support for transform functions in schema will go away.

## Documentation
TBD for gitbooks
Example config
```
"ingestionConfig": {
      "filterConfig": {
        "filterFunction": "Groovy({foo == \"VALUE1\"}, foo)"
      },
      "transformConfigs": [{
        "columnName": "bar",
        "transformFunction": "lower(moo)"
      },
      {
        "columnName": "hoursSinceEpoch",
        "transformFunction": "toEpochHours(millis)"
      }]
    }
```
